OL,3,CGrandmother scoops #1 million for
OL,4,Cfamily playing late husband's lottery
OL,5,Cnumbers
OL,7,FA grandmother scooped #1 million on
OL,8,Fthe lottery alongside her two children
OL,9,Fafter playing numbers chosen by her
OL,10,Flate husband years ago.
OL,12,FRetired office manager Rose Tresadern,
OL,13,F80, from near Southend in Essex, said
OL,14,Fit felt like Derek Tresadern was
OL,15,F"still looking out for us".
OL,17,FFormer business analyst Mr Tresadern
OL,18,Fwas 83 years old when he died
OL,19,Ffollowing a short illness last year,
OL,20,Fnot long after the couple celebrated
OL,21,Ftheir diamond wedding anniversary.
OL,26,@wD@AOUwD@ZO]
