OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1779948269
OL,3,CGrandmother scoops #1 million for
OL,4,Cfamily playing late husband's lottery
OL,5,Cnumbers
OL,7,FMrs Tresadern, together with children
OL,8,FBarry Tresadern, 52, and 57-year-old
OL,9,FJulie Tresadern, decided to continue
OL,10,Fplaying Mr Tresadern's Lotto numbers
OL,11,Fevery week in their family syndicate.
OL,13,FTheir numbers one, four, 12, 15 and
OL,14,F39, and the bonus ball, 48, came up in
OL,15,Fthe draw on April 18 as they matched
OL,16,Ffive main numbers out of six and the
OL,17,Fbonus ball.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G2/9
