OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1779948269
OL,3,CGrandmother scoops #1 million for
OL,4,Cfamily playing late husband's lottery
OL,5,Cnumbers
OL,7,FMrs Tresadern plans to use some of her
OL,8,Fshare of the #1 million winnings to
OL,9,Fmove to a retirement home better
OL,10,Fsuited to her mobility issues, and
OL,11,Fsome on a new ring to remind her of
OL,12,Fher late husband.
OL,14,F"We carried on playing the numbers
OL,15,Fbecause they reminded us of Derek,"
OL,16,Fsaid Mrs Tresadern.
OL,18,F"Winning #1 million never even crossed
OL,19,Four minds.
OL,26,@vD@AOUwD@cO]zD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/9
