OL,3,CGrandmother scoops #1 million for
OL,4,Cfamily playing late husband's lottery
OL,5,Cnumbers
OL,7,F"I rang Barry straight away, I could
OL,8,Fhardly speak," she said.
OL,10,F"They thought something terrible had
OL,11,Fhappened.
OL,13,F"When I told them we'd won #1 million,
OL,14,Fthere was just silence.
OL,16,F"None of us could believe it."
OL,18,FMrs Tresadern said the win "changes
OL,19,Feverything" and she plans to move into
OL,20,Fa more suitable home together with her
OL,21,FMaltese dog, Amira.
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@NO]rD@AOUuD@AOUxD@AOUxD@^O]zD@
